name: Domestic dog (Canis familiaris)[3]
breed: Extinct Pleistocene population of the grey wolf (Canis lupus ssp.)[4]

name: Domestic sheep (Ovis aries)[3]
breed: Possibly the Armenian mouflon (Ovis gmelini gmelini)

name: Domestic pig (Sus domesticus)
breed: Anatolian boar (Sus scrofa libycus),[13] Northern Chinese boar (Sus scrofa moupinensis)[14]

name: European cattle or taurine cattle (Bos taurus)[3][19][20]
Zebu, Brahman cattle, indicine cattle or humped cattle (Bos indicus)[3]
Domestic cat or house cat (Felis catus)[3]
breed: Common North African wildcat (Felis lybica lybica)[27]

name: Domestic chicken (Gallus gallus domesticus)
breed: Bangladesh red junglefowl (Gallus gallus murghi) with some contribution from the grey junglefowl (Gallus sonneratii)

name: Domestic donkey, domestic ass or burro (Equus asinus)
breed: African wild ass (Equus africanus), including subspecies Nubian (E. a. africanus) and Somali wild ass (E. a. somaliensis)[29]

name: Gayal (Bos frontalis)[3]
breed: Gayal (Bos frontalis) with significant introgression from other Bos species[32]

name: Western honey bee (Apis mellifera) including subspecies German (A. m. mellifera), Italian (A. m. ligustica), Carniolan (A. m. carnica), Caucasian (A. m. caucasia), Greek (A. m. cecropia), Saharan (A. m. sahariensis) and Egyptian honey bees (A. m. lamarckii)
age: 4000 BCE (the modern era for A. m. mellifera, the 1880s for A. m. ligustica, uncertain for A. m. carnica, A. m. caucasia, A. m. cecropia, A. m. sahariensis and A. m. lamarckii)

name: Domestic horse (Equus caballus)
breed: Extinct unknown population of the wild horse (Equus ferus), possibly the tarpan or European wild horse (E. f. ferus)†[38]

name: Domestic goose and domestic swan goose (Anser anser domesticus and Anser cygnoides domesticus)
breed: Greylag goose (Anser anser) and swan goose (A. cygnoides)
age: 3000 BCE for A. anser, date uncertain for A. cygnoides[42]

name: Domestic guineafowl (Numida meleagris domesticus)
breed: West African helmeted guineafowl (Numida meleagris galeatus)

name: Barbary dove or ringed turtle dove (Streptopelia risoria)
Domestic turkey (Meleagris gallopavo domesticus)
breed: South Mexican wild turkey (Meleagris gallopavo gallopavo)

name: Japanese quail (C. japonica) or Domesticated quail
Society finch or Bengalese finch (Lonchura striata domestica)
breed: White-rumped munia or striated finch (Lonchura striata swinhoei) with some contribution from the Indian silverbill or white-throated munia (Euodice malabarica)
age: unknown, may have been introduced to Japan sometime around the early 18th century CE[51]

name: Fancy mouse a.k.a. laboratory mouse (Mus musculus domestica)
breed: Western European house mouse (Mus musculus domesticus)

name: Fancy rat a.k.a. laboratory rat (Rattus norvegicus domestica)
Domesticated hedgehogs (Atelerix albiventris, A. algirus, Hemiechinus auritus and H. collaris)
breed: Four-toed (Atelerix albiventris), Algerian (A. algirus), long-eared (Hemiechinus auritus), and Indian long-eared hedgehog (H. collaris)
